po6
------------------------------------------
This is a library that includes all the code I tend to carry from project to
project for wrapping POSIX APIs for C++.  Where possible, things are
implemented inline so that there is minimal to no cost above and beyond using
the good old C APIs.

Runtime requirements:

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.24.51-6
  cygport-0.17.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-1
  gcc-g++-4.9.2-1
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/rescrv/po6

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/rescrv/po6/archive/releases/0.5.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack po6-0.5.2-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./po6-0.5.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/po6-0.5.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/po6-0.5.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(po6)
  /usr/include/po6/error.h
  /usr/include/po6/io/fd.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/hostname.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/ipaddr.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/location.h
  /usr/include/po6/net/socket.h
  /usr/include/po6/noncopyable.h
  /usr/include/po6/pathname.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/barrier.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/cond.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/mutex.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/rwlock.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/spinlock.h
  /usr/include/po6/threads/thread.h
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libpo6.pc
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/po6.README
  /usr/share/doc/po6/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/po6/README

